=== Former personalities ===
* [[E. D. Hill]], Weekdays co-host from 1998 to 2006, replaced by Gretchen Carlson.
* [[Dave Briggs (journalist)|Dave Briggs]], Weekend co-host, left at the end of 2012 to join NBC Sports Network <ref>{{cite news | work  = Inqusitir | url = http://www.inquisitr.com/461890/dave-briggs-leaves-fox-and-friends-with-emotional-on-air-farewell-video/ | title = Dave Briggs Leaves ‘Fox and Friends’ With Emotional On-Air Farewell [Video] | date = December 30, 2012 | accessdate = January 28, 2012}}</ref>
* [[Gretchen Carlson]], Weekdays co-host from 2006 to 2013, replaced by Elisabeth Hasselbeck; currently hosting the weekday afternoon ''[[The Real Story with Gretchen Carlson|The Real Story]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Elisabeth Hasselbeck leaving "The View" to join Fox|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-207_162-57592983/elisabeth-hasselbeck-leaving-the-view-for-fox/|publisher=cbsnews|accessdate=10 July 2013}}</ref>
* [[Alisyn Camerota]], Weekend co-host, left the program on September 28, 2013, to be the co-host of a new weekday version of ''[[America's News Headquarters]]'' airing on the network.<ref>{{cite web|last=Weprin|first=Alex|title=‘The Real Story with Gretchen Carlson’ To Debut At 2 PM On Fox News September 30|url=http://www.mediabistro.com/tvnewser/the-real-story-with-gretchen-carlson-to-debut-at-2-pm-on-fox-news-september-30_b198032|publisher=mediabistro.com|accessdate=28 September 2013}}</ref> Left Fox News in March of 2014 and joined CNN in July of 2014.

